<subSubSection id="35D3B8E2FF8FFFB1FF03FAA1FA9A3877" box="[199,1373,1340,1365]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="7D76EB69FF8FFFB1FF03FAA1FA9A3877" blockId="13.[151,1437,151,1904]" box="[199,1373,1340,1365]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">
<emphasis id="4FBD377BFF8FFFB1FF03FAA1FE813877" bold="true" box="[199,326,1340,1365]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">Etymology</emphasis>
. The epithet “ 
<taxonomicName id="BAC990EAFF8FFFB1FE22FAA1FDAE3877" box="[486,617,1340,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Recchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="volcanensis">
<emphasis id="4FBD377BFF8FFFB1FE22FAA1FDAE3877" box="[486,617,1340,1365]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">volcanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” refers to the 
<typeStatus id="A27255CBFF8FFFB1FCCDFAA0FCFE3877" box="[777,825,1341,1365]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">type</typeStatus>
locality of the 
<typeStatus id="A27255CBFF8FFFB1FC26FAA1FB833877" box="[994,1092,1340,1365]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">holotype</typeStatus>
(Refugio Los Volcanes).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="35D3B8E2FF8FFFB2FF03FAC2FA523C58" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="143" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="7D76EB69FF8FFFB1FF03FAC2FE633A0A" blockId="13.[151,1437,151,1904]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">
<emphasis id="4FBD377BFF8FFFB1FF03FAC2FEF3385A" bold="true" box="[199,308,1375,1400]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="BAC990EAFF8FFFB1FE81FAC2FDEB385A" box="[325,556,1375,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Recchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="volcanensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="4FBD377BFF8FFFB1FE81FAC2FDEB385A" box="[325,556,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">Recchia volcanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="548E8A00FF8FFFB1FDF2FAC2FD54385A" box="[566,659,1375,1400]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" rank="species">
<emphasis id="4FBD377BFF8FFFB1FDF2FAC2FD54385A" bold="true" box="[566,659,1375,1400]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="BAC990EAFF8FFFB1FCF5FAFCFB09385A" authority="Martins &amp; Galileo, 1998" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="1998" box="[817,1230,1375,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Recchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abauna">
<emphasis id="4FBD377BFF8FFFB1FCF5FAFCFC60385A" box="[817,935,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">R. abauna</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="19589698FF8FFFB1FC75FAC2FB09385A" author="Martins" box="[945,1230,1375,1400]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (1998) Revisao da tribo Aerenicini Lacordaire, 1872 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae). Arquivos de Zoologia, 35 (1), 1 - 133. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11606 / issn. 2176 - 7793. v 35 i 1 p 1 - 133" type="journal article" year="1998">Martins &amp; Galileo, 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the upper eye lobes distinctly wider, with more than 10 rows of ommatidia (
<figureCitation id="E5F2F7ECFF8FFFB1FC97FA19FC6F38BE" box="[851,936,1412,1437]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 – 33. 26 – 29" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1837,1860]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,390,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1435,373,1816]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 26 – 33. 26 – 29, Mecometopus martinsi sp. nov., holotype female: 26, dorsal habitus; 27, ventral habitus; 28, lateral habitus; 29, head, frontal view. 30, Recchia volcanensis sp. nov., holotype female, upper eye lobes. 31, Recchia lanei, holotype female, upper eye lobes. 32 – 33, Recchia procera, paratype female: 32, upper eye lobes; 33, elytral apices." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/167721/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
), by the pubescence on basal third of elytral disc not forming band, by the distal sixth of the elytra not entirely with whitish pubescence. In 
<taxonomicName id="BAC990EAFF8FFFB1FB7EFA34FAEB38E2" box="[1210,1324,1447,1472]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Recchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abauna">
<emphasis id="4FBD377BFF8FFFB1FB7EFA34FAEB38E2" box="[1210,1324,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">R. abauna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the upper eye lobes are narrower, with 5-6 rows of ommatidia (
<figureCitation id="E5F2F7ECFF8FFFB1FD3AFA51FC9338C6" box="[766,852,1484,1509]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 – 39. 34 – 36" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1919,1942]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,306,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1435,301,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 34 – 39. 34 – 36, Recchia volcanensis sp. nov., holotype female: 34, dorsal habitus; 35, ventral habitus; 36, lateral habitus. 37, Recchia abauna, paratype female. 38, Recchia procera, paratype female. 39, Recchia lanei, holotype female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/167722/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
), the pubescence on basal discal third of the elytra forms band, the distal sixth of the elytra is entirely covered with whitish pubescence. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="BAC990EAFF8FFFB1FADEFA6CFEE83B0E" authority="Lane, 1939" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1939" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Recchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distincta">
<emphasis id="4FBD377BFF8FFFB1FADEFA6CFA5B3B2A" box="[1306,1436,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">R. distincta</emphasis>
(Lane, 1939)
</taxonomicName>
mainly by the upper eye lobes wider and with finer ommatidia (narrower and with coarser ommatidia). It can be separated from 
<taxonomicName id="BAC990EAFF8FFFB1FD8AF9A4FC173B72" authority="Martins &amp; Galileo, 1985" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="1985" box="[590,976,1591,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Recchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanei">
<emphasis id="4FBD377BFF8FFFB1FD8AF9A4FD6E3B72" box="[590,681,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">R. lanei</emphasis>
Martins &amp; Galileo, 1985
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="E5F2F7ECFF8FFFB1FC26F9AAFBF03B72" box="[994,1079,1591,1616]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 – 39. 34 – 36" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1919,1942]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,306,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1435,301,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 34 – 39. 34 – 36, Recchia volcanensis sp. nov., holotype female: 34, dorsal habitus; 35, ventral habitus; 36, lateral habitus. 37, Recchia abauna, paratype female. 38, Recchia procera, paratype female. 39, Recchia lanei, holotype female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/167722/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
) by the upper eye lobes wider (narrower in 
<taxonomicName id="BAC990EAFF8FFFB1FEEEF9C0FE463B57" box="[298,385,1628,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Recchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanei">
<emphasis id="4FBD377BFF8FFFB1FEEEF9C0FE463B57" box="[298,385,1628,1653]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">R. lanei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- 
<figureCitation id="E5F2F7ECFF8FFFB1FE5DF9C1FE2D3B56" box="[409,490,1628,1653]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 – 33. 26 – 29" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1837,1860]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,390,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1435,373,1816]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 26 – 33. 26 – 29, Mecometopus martinsi sp. nov., holotype female: 26, dorsal habitus; 27, ventral habitus; 28, lateral habitus; 29, head, frontal view. 30, Recchia volcanensis sp. nov., holotype female, upper eye lobes. 31, Recchia lanei, holotype female, upper eye lobes. 32 – 33, Recchia procera, paratype female: 32, upper eye lobes; 33, elytral apices." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/167721/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
) and by the pubescence forming different drawings on the elytra (
<figureCitation id="E5F2F7ECFF8FFFB1FB16F9C1FAE03B56" box="[1234,1319,1628,1653]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 – 39. 34 – 36" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1919,1942]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,306,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1435,301,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 34 – 39. 34 – 36, Recchia volcanensis sp. nov., holotype female: 34, dorsal habitus; 35, ventral habitus; 36, lateral habitus. 37, Recchia abauna, paratype female. 38, Recchia procera, paratype female. 39, Recchia lanei, holotype female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/167722/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
). It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="BAC990EAFF8FFFB1FF10F91CFE2C3BBA" authority="Lane, 1966" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1966" box="[212,491,1663,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Recchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludibriosa">
<emphasis id="4FBD377BFF8FFFB1FF10F91CFEA13BBA" box="[212,358,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">R. ludibriosa</emphasis>
Lane, 1966
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="BAC990EAFF8FFFB1FDE5F91CFC6C3BBA" authority="Martins &amp; Galileo, 1998" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="1998" box="[545,939,1663,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Recchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moema">
<emphasis id="4FBD377BFF8FFFB1FDE5F91CFD563BBA" box="[545,657,1665,1688]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">R. moema</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="19589698FF8FFFB1FD5CF9E2FC6C3BBA" author="Martins" box="[664,939,1663,1688]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (1998) Revisao da tribo Aerenicini Lacordaire, 1872 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae). Arquivos de Zoologia, 35 (1), 1 - 133. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11606 / issn. 2176 - 7793. v 35 i 1 p 1 - 133" type="journal article" year="1998">Martins &amp; Galileo, 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
mainly by the pubescence forming different drawings on the elytra (see photographs of the 
<typeStatus id="A27255CBFF8FFFB1FD66F939FCC83B9F" box="[674,783,1700,1725]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">holotypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="BAC990EAFF8FFFB1FCF7F938FC023B9F" box="[819,965,1700,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Recchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludibriosa">
<emphasis id="4FBD377BFF8FFFB1FCF7F938FC023B9F" box="[819,965,1700,1725]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">R. ludibriosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="BAC990EAFF8FFFB1FC3FF938FBAC3B9E" box="[1019,1131,1701,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Recchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moema">
<emphasis id="4FBD377BFF8FFFB1FC3FF938FBAC3B9E" box="[1019,1131,1701,1724]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">R. moema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at 
<bibRefCitation id="19589698FF8FFFB1FB48F939FAD83B9F" author="Bezark" box="[1164,1311,1700,1725]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" refString="Bezark, L. G. (2016) A photographic Catalog of the Cerambycidae of the New World. Available from: https: // apps 2. cdfa. ca. gov / publicApps / plant / bycidDB / wsearch. asp? w = n (accessed 20 June 2016)" type="journal article" year="2016">Bezark 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Finally, it differs from 
<taxonomicName id="BAC990EAFF8FFFB1FEE9F954FD103BC2" authority="Martins &amp; Galileo, 1985" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="1985" box="[301,727,1735,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Recchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="procera">
<emphasis id="4FBD377BFF8FFFB1FEE9F954FE6D3BC2" box="[301,426,1737,1760]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">R. procera</emphasis>
Martins &amp; Galileo, 1985
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="E5F2F7ECFF8FFFB1FD2FF95AFC863BC2" box="[747,833,1735,1760]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 – 39. 34 – 36" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1919,1942]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,306,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1435,301,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 34 – 39. 34 – 36, Recchia volcanensis sp. nov., holotype female: 34, dorsal habitus; 35, ventral habitus; 36, lateral habitus. 37, Recchia abauna, paratype female. 38, Recchia procera, paratype female. 39, Recchia lanei, holotype female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/167722/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
) by the body wider, by the upper eye lobes wider (narrower in 
<taxonomicName id="BAC990EAFF8FFFB1FEEEF970FE663A26" box="[298,417,1773,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Recchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="procera">
<emphasis id="4FBD377BFF8FFFB1FEEEF970FE663A26" box="[298,417,1773,1796]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">R. procera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="E5F2F7ECFF8FFFB1FE75F971FDC43A26" box="[433,515,1772,1797]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 – 33. 26 – 29" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1837,1860]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,390,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1435,373,1816]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 26 – 33. 26 – 29, Mecometopus martinsi sp. nov., holotype female: 26, dorsal habitus; 27, ventral habitus; 28, lateral habitus; 29, head, frontal view. 30, Recchia volcanensis sp. nov., holotype female, upper eye lobes. 31, Recchia lanei, holotype female, upper eye lobes. 32 – 33, Recchia procera, paratype female: 32, upper eye lobes; 33, elytral apices." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/167721/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
)), and by the elytral apex distinctly wider and rounded (
<figureCitation id="E5F2F7ECFF8FFFB1FBB9F971FB083A26" box="[1149,1231,1772,1797]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 – 39. 34 – 36" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1919,1942]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,306,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1435,301,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 34 – 39. 34 – 36, Recchia volcanensis sp. nov., holotype female: 34, dorsal habitus; 35, ventral habitus; 36, lateral habitus. 37, Recchia abauna, paratype female. 38, Recchia procera, paratype female. 39, Recchia lanei, holotype female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/167722/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) (more acuminate in 
<taxonomicName id="BAC990EAFF8FFFB1FF70F88CFEEC3A0A" box="[180,299,1809,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Recchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="procera">
<emphasis id="4FBD377BFF8FFFB1FF70F88CFEEC3A0A" box="[180,299,1809,1832]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">R. procera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="E5F2F7ECFF8FFFB1FEFEF892FE4B3A0A" box="[314,396,1807,1832]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 – 33. 26 – 29" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1837,1860]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,390,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1435,373,1816]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 26 – 33. 26 – 29, Mecometopus martinsi sp. nov., holotype female: 26, dorsal habitus; 27, ventral habitus; 28, lateral habitus; 29, head, frontal view. 30, Recchia volcanensis sp. nov., holotype female, upper eye lobes. 31, Recchia lanei, holotype female, upper eye lobes. 32 – 33, Recchia procera, paratype female: 32, upper eye lobes; 33, elytral apices." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/167721/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
)).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7D76EB69FF8FFFB1FF03F8A9FCFE3A52" blockId="13.[151,1437,151,1904]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">
<taxonomicName id="BAC990EAFF8FFFB1FF03F8A9FE6C3A6F" box="[199,427,1844,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Recchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="volcanensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="4FBD377BFF8FFFB1FF03F8A9FE6C3A6F" box="[199,427,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">Recchia volcanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="548E8A00FF8FFFB1FE76F8A9FDCC3A6F" box="[434,523,1844,1869]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" rank="species">
<emphasis id="4FBD377BFF8FFFB1FE76F8A9FDCC3A6F" bold="true" box="[434,523,1844,1869]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be included in the alternative of couplet “14” from 
<bibRefCitation id="19589698FF8FFFB1FBB9F8A9FA5B3A6E" author="Martins" box="[1149,1436,1844,1869]" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (1998) Revisao da tribo Aerenicini Lacordaire, 1872 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae). Arquivos de Zoologia, 35 (1), 1 - 133. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11606 / issn. 2176 - 7793. v 35 i 1 p 1 - 133" type="journal article" year="1998">Martins &amp; Galileo (1998)</bibRefCitation>
